    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1924-04-11T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1924-04-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="488"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d488">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">891.77/52</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        British Ambassador</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Howard</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <p>The Secretary of State presents his compliments to His Excellency the British
                    Ambassador and has the honor to acknowledge the receipt of the communication of
                    March 12, 1924—No. 226—transmitting copies of certain documents relating to the
                    claim of British interests to railway rights in Persia and indicating the
                    attitude of His Majesty’s Government respecting the cooperation of American
                    firms with the Persian Railway Syndicate. Due note has been taken of the views
                    expressed in this communication and of the copies of documents transmitted
                    therewith.</p>
                <closer>
                    <dateline rendition="#left">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1924-04-11">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 11, 1924</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
